<p>Ok, I know I&#8217;ve whinged about <a href="http://natalian.org/archives/2006/04/02/copy-and-paste/">Copy &amp; Paste</a> before. It just seems to have got worse. Maybe I am becoming more inept.</p>

<p>Though I have a dream. A dream whereby I can copy and paste the <span class="caps">URL</span> bar of my Firefox with:</p>

<ol>
<li><span class="caps">CTRL</span>+L</li>
<li><span class="caps">CTRL</span>+C</li>
<li>Alt+1 (switch to uxterm)</li>
<li>Middle click into uxterm or shift+insert on keyboard</li>
</ol>

<p>Instead of the nightmare right now:</p>

<ol>
<li><span class="caps">CTRL</span>+L</li>
<li><span class="caps">CTRL</span>+C</li>
<li>Alt+1 (switch to uxterm)</li>
<li>Middle click into uxterm</li>
<li>Wrong text! (if you are using vim and pasting a lot of text, hilarious consequences ensue)</li>
<li>Undo damage </li>
<li>Alt+2 (switch to firefox)</li>
<li>Find correct tab</li>
<li><span class="caps">CTRL</span>+L</li>
<li>Double click with <span class="caps">LMB</span> (i hate having to use the mouse here)</li>
<li>Pray</li>
<li>Double click with <span class="caps">LMB</span> again just to be sure</li>
<li>Alt+1 (switch to uxterm)</li>
<li>Middle click into uxterm</li>
</ol>

